content: Visually inventive hidden object puzzler that propels a wordless story. Short (5 chapters) & unlike any other Artifex Mundi game out there. Brother Rabbit helps his friend, but in the background, cut-scenes tell a real world story. Good though it is, it's length let's it down & I'm uncertain whether the virtually blank screens between most chapters, except 2 & 3 are supposed to be so. Are there cut-scenes between all levels & they aren't loading? I'm unsure. Ultimately it's a brief pleasure.

I got this game for my tablet after falling in love with it on my PC. Now I can play with my granddaughter. That the game is almost completely non-verbal. That it's low-tech.
